&lt;p&gt;The Max Planck Institute for Astrophysics (MPA) has awarded the Rudolf-Kippenhahn-Prize for the best scientific paper by a student to Silvia Almada Monter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Silvia received the award for her paper titled &amp;ldquo;Crossing walls and windows: the curious escape of Lyman-Î± photons through ionized channels&amp;rdquo;. Her research challenges existing assumptions about how Lyman-alpha photons escape from galaxies, proposing a new physical picture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The prize recognizes originality, scientific impact, and the quality of writing in publications where students made substantial contributions.&lt;/p&gt;
